MoInflAffixSlot.Name: Abs/Plural
MoInflAffixSlot.Description: Contains the absolutive or normal plurals.

MoInflAffixSlot.Name: Possessed Plural
MoInflAffixSlot.Description: Contains the possessed plural marker.

MoInflAffixSlot.Name: Possessor
MoInflAffixSlot.Description: Contains the nominal possessors.

MoInflAffixSlot.Name: Loan Plural
MoInflAffixSlot.Description: Contains plural forms used with nominal loan words.

MoInflAffixSlot.Name: Diminutive
MoInflAffixSlot.Description: Contains the diminutive or honorific suffix.

MoInflAffixSlot.Name: Exceptional Plural
MoInflAffixSlot.Description: Contains the plural forms that the exceptional nouns can take.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Native noun
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An unpossessed native noun must have either the absolutive suffix or a plural suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Possessed native noun
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A possessed native noun must have a possessor prefix. If it is plural, then it also must have the possessive plural. It also may take the diminutive/honorific suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Predicate nominal on a native noun.
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A predicate nominal may be formed by putting a verbal subject prefix on a well-formed native noun.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Predicate nominal on a possessed native noun.
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A predicate nominal may be formed by putting a verbal subject prefix on a well-formed possessed native noun.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Inalienably possessed noun
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An inalienably possessed noun must have a possessor prefix. If the prefix is plural, then there also must be a plural suffix. It also may take the diminutive/honorific suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Predicate nominal on an inalienably possessed noun.
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A predicate nominal may be formed by putting a verbal subject prefix on a well-formed inalienably possessed noun.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: A (Spanish) loan noun
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A noun which is borrowed from Spanish may have a plural suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: A possessed (Spanish) loan noun
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A possessed noun borrowed from Spanish must have a possessor prefix and may have a possessed plural suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Predicate nominal on a possessed (Spanish) loan noun.
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A predicate nominal may be formed by putting a verbal subject prefix on a well-formed possessed (Spanish) loan noun.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Exceptional native nouns
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: Exceptional nouns do not require the absolutive, but may take a plural.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Predicate nominal on an exceptional noun.
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A predicate nominal may be formed by putting a verbal subject prefix on a well-formed exceptional native noun.

MoInflClass.Name: Class I
MoInflClass.Description: Verbs in class I take -k to indicate preterit singular. They tend to have the shape CCV or VCV where the C is t, tl, or k and the final vowel is a.

MoInflClass.Name: Class II
MoInflClass.Description: Verbs in class II have a shape of VCV and lose the final vowel in the preterit.

MoInflClass.Name: Class III
MoInflClass.Description: Verbs in class III end in ia or ova.

MoInflClass.Name: Class IV
MoInflClass.Description: Verbs in class IV take -h to form the preterit singular.

MoStemName.Name: Class II (Perfective root)
MoStemName.Description: Verbs of inflection class II truncate final vowel in preterite, pluperfect, durative, and -ti connector ones.

MoStemName.Name: Class III ("regular")
MoStemName.Description: Verbs of inflection class III retain final /a/ or /va/ in present, imperfect, and conditional. In most other instances, neither the final /a/ nor /va/ are present.

MoStemName.Name: Class III (has h)
MoStemName.Description: Verbs of inflection class III convert final /a/ or /va/ to /h/ in pluperfect, -ti connectors, and durative.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Intransitive present indicative or interrogative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A present intransitive verb has a subject prefix, possibly a directional prefix, an intransitive verb stem, and then a portmanteau imperfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Intransitive future indicative or interrogative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A future intransitive verb has a subject prefix, possibly a directional prefix, an intransitive verb stem, the future marker, and then a portmanteau perfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Intransitive past indicative or interrogtative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A past tense intransitive verb has a past prefix, a subject prefix, possibly a directional prefix, an intransitive verb stem and then a portmanteau perfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Intransitive imperfect indicative or interrogative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An imperfect intransitive verb has a past prefix, a subject prefix, possibly a directional prefix, an intransitive verb stem, the imperfect marker and then a portmanteau imperfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Intransitive imperative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An intransitive imperative verb has a subjunctive subject prefix, possibly a directional prefix, an intransitive verb stem, and then an optional subjunctive number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Intransitive subjunctive verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An intransitive subjunctive verb has a subjunctive subject prefix, possibly a directional prefix, an intransitive verb stem, and then an optional subjunctive number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive present indicative or interrogative verb

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive future indicative or interrogative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A future transitive verb has a subject prefix, an object prefix, possibly a 3rd plural object prefix, a transitive verb stem, the future marker, and then a portmanteau perfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive future indicative or interrogative verb with subject-object portmanteau prefixes
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A future transitive verb has a portmanteau subject/object prefix, possibly a directional prefix, possibly a 3rd plural object prefix, a transitive verb stem, the future marker, and then a portmanteau perfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive past indicative or interrogative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A past transitive verb has a past prefix, a subject prefix, an object prefix, possibly a directional prefix, possibly a 3rd plural object prefix, a transitive verb stem and then a portmanteau perfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive past indicative or interrogative verb with subject-object portmanteau prefixes

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive imperfect indicative or interrogative verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An imperfect transitive verb has a past prefix, a subject prefix, an object prefix, possibly a directional prefix, possibly a 3rd plural object prefix, a transitive verb stem, the imperfect marker and then a portmanteau imperfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive imperfect indicative or interrogative verb with subject-object portmanteau prefixes
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An imperfect transitive verb has a past prefix, a portmanteau subject/object prefix, possibly a directional prefix, possibly a 3rd plural object prefix, a transitive verb stem, the imperfect marker and then a portmanteau imperfective/number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: An imperative transitive verb has an imperative (subject) prefix, an object prefix, possibly a directional prefix, possibly a 3rd plural object prefix, a transitive verb stem and an optional imperative number suffix.

MoInflAffixTemplate.Name: Transitive subjunctive verb
MoInflAffixTemplate.Description: A subjunctive transitive verb has a subjunctive subject prefix, an object prefix, possibly a directional prefix, possibly a 3rd plural object prefix, a transitive verb stem and a subjunctive number suffix.

MoInflClass.Description: Adjectives of this class take the -eh form of the plural.

MoInflClass.Name: Uses reduplication for plural
MoInflClass.Description: Adjectives of this class use reduplication to form the plural.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Noun-noun compound
MoEndoCompound.Description: In a noun-noun compound, the first noun modifes the second noun. Possible meanings include: the second noun is made of the first; the second noun is located in the first; the second noun forms part of the first; or the second noun comes from the first. In some cases, the nouns are in apposition to each other.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Adjective-noun compound
MoEndoCompound.Description: In an adjective-noun compound, the adjective modifes the head noun.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Noun incorporation on transitive verb.
MoEndoCompound.Description: Some nouns can be incorporated into the stem which do not effect the (agreement marker reflection of) the transitivty of the head. These tend to be body parts. The incorporated noun may be interpreted as part of the object or of the subject. Sometimes the subject of the verb is the possessor of the incorporated body part. Sometimes the incorporated noun is a secondary object.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Noun incorporation on intransitive verb.
MoEndoCompound.Description: Some nouns can be incorporated into the stem which do not effect the (agreement marker reflection of) the intransitivty of the head. These tend to be body parts. Sometimes the subject of the verb is the possessor of the incorporated body part.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Adjective incorporation on a verb
MoEndoCompound.Description: An adjective may be incorporated into a verb stem.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Postposition incorporation on a verb
MoEndoCompound.Description: A postposition may be incorporated into a verb stem.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Adverb incorporation on a verb
MoEndoCompound.Description: An adverb may be incorporated into a verb stem.

MoEndoCompound.Name: Object incorporation
MoEndoCompound.Description: In an object incorporation compound, the nominal object of the transitive verb is the left member of the compound. The verb is the head. The result is an intransitive verb.
